---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Containing MO — Scrabble Word List & Strategy"
  description="Complete list of Scrabble words containing MO with scores, definitions, and strategic tips. Master MO words for better Scrabble plays."
  keywords="scrabble words containing mo, mo words scrabble, words with mo, scrabble mo word list, mo scrabble strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Containing MO — Scrabble Word List & Strategy",
    "description": "Complete list of Scrabble words containing MO with scores, definitions, and strategic tips.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-mo" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the highest-scoring MO words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top MO words include MONKEYISH (19 pts), MONARCHY (18 pts), MONOPOLY (15 pts), MEMORY (13 pts), and PROMOTE (11 pts). MO appears in 600+ valid Scrabble words." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many Scrabble words contain MO?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Over 600 valid Scrabble words contain MO. Common examples include MORE, MOST, MONEY, AMONG, ALMOST, DEMON, MEMORY, and PROMOTE." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What strategy works best with MO tiles?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "MO is a versatile pair with 600+ words. MO- prefix words (MORE, MOST, MOVE, MOON) are strong openers. The -MON pattern (DEMON, LEMON, COMMON) and -MOTE/-MORE endings extend well. MONOPOLY (15 pts) and MONARCHY (18 pts) are premium bingo candidates." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Letter Pair Content</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Containing MO — Scrabble Word List & Strategy</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">MO is a versatile letter pair appearing in over 600 valid Scrabble words. From everyday plays like MORE and MOST to premium targets like MONARCHY (18 pts) and MONOPOLY (15 pts), MO provides strong scoring routes. The MO- prefix alone gives dozens of openers, while the -MON and -MOTE patterns extend naturally toward bingo territory.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top MO Words by Score</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Definition</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MONKEYISH</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">19</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Resembling a monkey</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MONARCHY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Rule by a king or queen</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MONOPOLY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Exclusive market control</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MEMORY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">The faculty of recall</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PROMOTE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To advance in rank</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MONEY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Currency</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ALMOST</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Nearly</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">DEMON</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">An evil spirit</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">AMONG</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">In the middle of</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MOON</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Earths satellite</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MORE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Greater in amount</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">600+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid MO words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Average score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Common</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Pair frequency</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips for MO Words</h2>

      <p>MO- prefix words (MORE, MOST, MOVE, MOON, MOUNT) are reliable openers on any board. The -MON ending (DEMON, LEMON, COMMON, SUMMON) works well for parallel plays. The -MOTE and -MOLE patterns provide hook-friendly extensions. MONARCHY (18 pts) and MONOPOLY (15 pts) are achievable bingo targets when you have the right rack balance of consonants and vowels.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MONKEYISH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">19 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MONARCHY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MONOPOLY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MEMORY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PROMOTE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MONEY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10 pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Key Takeaway</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">MO provides <span class="text-white font-medium">600+ valid words</span> with strong prefix and suffix flexibility. MONARCHY (18 pts) and MONOPOLY (15 pts) are premium bingo targets. MONEY (10 pts) and DEMON (8 pts) are reliable everyday plays that keep your options open.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-qu/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Containing QU — Essential Scrabble Q Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-multiple-vowels/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words With Multiple Vowels — Scrabble Vowel Dumps</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/four-letter-words-every-player-should-know/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Four-Letter Words Every Scrabble Player Should Know</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every MO word from your tiles — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
